Requirements

1. Functional Requirements
	‚Ä¢	Display Notifications
	‚Ä¢	Show a list of notifications categorized by type: Report, Project, CPD, Referee, System.
	‚Ä¢	Display title, description, timestamp, and status (read/unread).
	‚Ä¢	Show an icon and image based on the notification type.
	‚Ä¢	Notification Filters & Search
	‚Ä¢	Allow users to search for notifications using keywords.
	‚Ä¢	Provide a filter dropdown to show:
	‚Ä¢	All notifications
	‚Ä¢	Unread only
	‚Ä¢	Reports
	‚Ä¢	Projects
	‚Ä¢	CPD
	‚Ä¢	Referees
	‚Ä¢	System
	‚Ä¢	Enable users to toggle between tabs for All, Unread, and Archive.
	‚Ä¢	Notification Actions
	‚Ä¢	Users can mark notifications as read/unread.
	‚Ä¢	Users can mark all notifications as read.
	‚Ä¢	Provide an option to archive notifications.
	‚Ä¢	Users can disable specific types of notifications.
	‚Ä¢	Navigation
	‚Ä¢	Clicking on a notification should take the user to the relevant section (e.g., reports, projects).
	‚Ä¢	Users can open a dropdown for more options (mark as read, archive, disable notifications).
	‚Ä¢	Unread Count
	‚Ä¢	Display the number of unread notifications at the top of the page.

‚∏ª

2. Non-Functional Requirements
	‚Ä¢	Performance
	‚Ä¢	Ensure fast rendering of notifications using efficient state management.
	‚Ä¢	Debounce search queries to optimize performance.
	‚Ä¢	Accessibility
	‚Ä¢	Ensure all UI elements have appropriate ARIA labels.
	‚Ä¢	Maintain color contrast for readability.
	‚Ä¢	Security
	‚Ä¢	Ensure notifications are fetched securely from the backend.
	‚Ä¢	Implement role-based access control (RBAC) so only authorized users can view certain notifications.
	‚Ä¢	Scalability
	‚Ä¢	The notification system should handle hundreds of notifications per user.
	‚Ä¢	Consider implementing pagination if needed.

